<Document>
<name>Great Dolomites Road — SS48</name>
<description><![CDATA[<h2>Great Dolomites Road — SS48</h2><p><i>South Tyrol / Veneto, Italy · SS48, Bolzano to Cortina d'Ampezzo</i></p><p><b>Four high passes through pale limestone peaks: Karer, Pordoi, Sella, Falzarego.</b></p><table style='font-family:sans-serif'><tr><td><b>Approx. length:</b></td><td>67 km (42 mi)</td></tr><tr><td><b>Drive time:</b></td><td>4 hrs no stops; ideally 2 days</td></tr><tr><td><b>Best season:</b></td><td>Late June–September; foliage early October</td></tr><tr><td><b>Watch out for:</b></td><td>Motorcycles in formation, snow at passes Oct–May, narrow shoulders, vertigo on Falzarego</td></tr><tr><td><b>Track points:</b></td><td>142</td></tr></table><hr><p>The Strada delle Dolomiti was completed in 1909, decades before tourism made these mountains famous. The Dolomites were named for the French geologist Déodat de Dolomieu, who in 1791 first described the magnesium-carbonate rock that gives them their distinctive ghost-white shade. At sunset, the rock blazes pink — the Ladin people of these valleys have a legend about a rose garden enchanted into stone. Drive the full route in a day for four passes; stay overnight in a Ladin valley to actually see the alpenglow. Cortina d'Ampezzo, at the eastern end, hosted the 1956 and 2026 Winter Olympics.</p><h3>Scenic points marked on this route:</h3><ul><li><b>Lago di Carezza</b> — Emerald-turquoise tarn reflecting the Latemar massif. Grimms-fairytale water; a 200 m walking loop. Best at midday when the light is on the peaks.</li><li><b>Canazei</b> — Classic Ladin alpine village in the Val di Fassa. The Sella Group rises behind — a four-sided fortress massif that defines what 'a Dolomite' looks like.</li><li><b>Passo Pordoi</b> — 2,239 m. Cable car up to Sass Pordoi at 2,950 m for a 360° panorama. WWI Italian war cemetery is the largest in the Alps — 8,582 dead.</li><li><b>Passo Falzarego</b> — 2,105 m. Cable car to Lagazuoi (2,778 m); WWI tunnels still walkable through the mountain (helmet, headlamp, 1.5 hr).</li><li><b>Cinque Torri</b> — Five free-standing rock towers preserved with WWI front-line trenches between them. Open-air museum.</li><li><b>Cortina d'Ampezzo</b> — 1956 + 2026 Winter Olympics; chic Italian Alpine town, dolomite peaks on three sides. Drive up to Tre Cime di Lavaredo (Lago di Misurina spur) for one of Europe's iconic mountain views.</li></ul><hr><p><i>Track geometry is interpolated between named waypoints — use a routing service to snap to actual road for navigation. Waypoints, scenic POIs, and notes are reliable.</i></p>]]></description>
